net.dean.jraw.models

Class Listing<T extends RedditObject>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dean.jraw.models.JsonModel
      • net.dean.jraw.models.RedditObject
        • net.dean.jraw.models.Listing<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of elements that will be in this listing
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.List<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FauxListing

    @Model(kind=LISTING)
public class Listing<T extends RedditObject>
extends RedditObject
implements java.util.List<T>
    Represents a listing of Things. A Listing has four main keys: before, after, modhash, and its children. Listing uses an ArrayList to implement the method inherited by List. Any method that attempts to change the data externally (such as List.remove(Object)) will throw an UnsupportedOperationException. List is only modifiable internally via loadMoreChildren.

      • loadMoreChildren

        public java.util.List<Comment> loadMoreChildren(RedditClient client,
                                                Submission parentSubmission,
                                                Comment commentRoot,
                                                CommentSort sort)
                                         throws NetworkException,
                                                ApiException,
                                                java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Loads more children into the Listing. The highest level modified will be commentRoot, or parentSubmission is commentRoot is null. All loaded children are inserted into the comment tree.
        Parameters:
        parentSubmission - The submission all comments are under
        commentRoot - If loading more comments, the parent comment of this listing or null if the parent is the submission
        sort - How to sort the recieved comments
        Returns:
        The array of comments loaded and inserted into the tree
        Throws:
        NetworkException
        ApiException
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If commentRoot

      • formCommentTree

        public static void formCommentTree(java.util.List<Comment> comments,
                                   java.util.List<More> mores)
                            throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Merge the Comments and Mores into a tree as far as possible. There should only be at most one more object left at completion; the More for the root of all the trees formed.
        Parameters:
        comments - The comments to organize into a tree
        mores - The mores to add into the comment tree
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If more than one More was left over, should only be one for the root
